The inventor of the World Wide Web intends to create a new Internet to compete with Google and Facebook
Tim Berners-Lee, inventor of the World Wide Web, created a startup that aims to rival Facebook, Amazon and Google.
The latest project of this legendary character of technologies, Inrupt, is a company that takes advantage of the open source platform of Berners-Lee, Solid.
This allows users to decide where their data is stored and who has access to that information.
In an exclusive interview with Fast Company, Berners-Lee joked that the underlying intention of Inrupt is to "dominate the world".
"We have to do it now," he said with regard to startup.
"It's a historic moment."
The application uses Solid's technology to allow people to create their own "personal online data storage", or POD.
It may contain contact lists, job lists, calendar, music library, and other personal and professional tools.
It's like Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify are all available in one browser at the same time.
What is unique about the personal online data store is that it is up to the user only to decide who has access to what kind of information.
The company calls it "personal capacity through the data."
The idea of Inrupt, according to CEO John Bruce, is to provide adequate resources, processes and skills to help make Solid available to everyone.
The company is currently composed of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, some internal programmers hired to work on the project and a community of volunteer programmers.
Starting this week, technology creators around the world will be able to create their own decentralised applications using the tools available on the Inrupt website.
Berners-Lee stated that he and his team are not talking to "Facebook and Google about whether or not to introduce a total change in which all their business models are turned upside down overnight.
"We're not asking for permission."
In a publication on Medium on Saturday, Berners-Lee wrote that "Inrupt's mission is to create commercial energy and an ecosystem that helps protect the integrity and quality of the new Web created with Solid".
